  "doc_id": "19387",
  "text": "A second purpose of the present study was to investigate a variable that could have facilitated children's mental state understanding and been confounded with mother mental state talk in the [CITATION_1] study. We investigated whether mothers' general parenting style (e.g. warmth, negative affect, responsiveness, teaching attempts, social skill/sensitivity and control level) rather than their mental state talk, facilitated children's theory of mind. For instance, a warm, sensitive parent might also be likely to provide many mental state utterances, but it would be unclear whether it was the warmth/sensitivity or the mental state utterances that facilitated children's theory of mind. It is possible that warm, sensitive parenting (mothers' actions with others) indirectly teaches children about peoples' feelings and perspectives irrespective of what mothers say.",
